Arsenal's Olivier Giroud and Arsene Wenger have been named as the Barclays Premier League Player and Manager of the Month for March - with the France striker thwarting Harry Kane's bid for a third award in a row.

Giroud netted five times in Arsenal's four consecutive league wins last month as Wenger's side took all 12 points on offer.

The Gunners are now a point behind second-placed Manchester City with eight games remaining.

